latestPosts.caption:
Week 22 was about prioritizing my rest and recovery being after my half marathon. My legs were SOO sore the next 2 days, so I really focused on having supplement drinks (loving the @youtheory.can collagen & @better_daysco greens), doing slow movements like pilates, stretches, nourishing my body with whole foods and taking it easy😌 

I let myself relax more so that I could recover quicker! Side note, I’ve been so obsessed with making matcha chia pudding and adding it to my yogurt bowls!!💚✨🙈

Here’s your reminder to allow yourself to rest!! Recovery and rest days are a super important part of training 💕

Come back every week for a new vlog & new goal on my journey of becoming my best self🫶🏼🎀
.

Week 20 I worked on perfecting my at home matcha latte making skills! Sharing some Matcha tips I learnt at a recent matcha workshop at Camellia sinensis !!🍵💚

- keep your matcha in the fridge (no sunlight)

- water should be about 75 Celsius 

- 3 grams of matcha per latte

- whisk in a “W” motion, you want it to be foamy! 

- if you’re adding sweetener, put sugar cane with the matcha before the water & then whisk, if it’s liquid sugar like honey, add it at the end 

Using the Camellia Sinensis matcha sora!! 🍵 my next goal for matcha is learning how to make a cold foam & cloud matcha!!
